.TH SPIKETRACE-VIEW 1 "February 2026" "spiketrace 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
spiketrace-view \- interactive TUI viewer for spiketrace dumps
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B spiketrace-view
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B spiketrace-view
is an interactive terminal user interface (TUI) for analyzing spike dumps
created by
.BR spiketrace (1).
It automatically discovers JSON files in /var/lib/spiketrace and provides
a navigable interface for inspecting anomalies.
.SH INTERFACE
The viewer is divided into three panels:
.TP
.B Explorer (Left)
List of all captured dumps, sorted by time.
.TP
.B Trigger (Top Right)
Details of the anomaly that triggered the snapshot.
.TP
.B Details (Bottom Right)
Process list for the selected snapshot, showing CPU, memory, and persistence.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.TP
.B Tab
Switch focus between Explorer and Details panels.
.TP
.BR j ", " "Down Arrow"
Move cursor down.
.TP
.BR k ", " "Up Arrow"
Move cursor up.
.TP
.B Enter
Load selected dump file.
.TP
.BR ] ", " n
Next snapshot (time travel forward).
.TP
.BR [ ", " p
Previous snapshot (time travel backward).
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/lib/spiketrace/
Default directory for spike dumps.
.SH NOTES
To read dumps created by the root-owned daemon, users must be members of
the
.B spiketrace
group:
.RS
.nf
sudo usermod \-aG spiketrace $USER
.fi
.RE
